@startuml
title RTP Consumer - Message flow (GPD -> RTP)

actor "GPD EventHub" as EH
participant "rtp-consumer" as C
participant "mil-auth" as MA
participant "rtp-sender" as S
queue "Dead letter queue" as DLQ

note over EH,C
A message is published on GPD EventHub.
rtp-consumer receives it asynchronously.
end note

EH -> C : EventReceived(message)\n(headers + payload)

note right of C
Step 1 - Message validation
- Syntactic validation (schema, required fields)
end note

C -> C : validate(message)

alt VALIDATION FAILED
  note right of C
  The message is malformed or invalid.
  It is published to the Dead letter queue for reprocessing.
  end note

  C -> DLQ : Publish(originalMessage + failure)\nmetadata: httpStatus, errorMessage, timestamp
  DLQ --> C : ack
  C --> EH : ack

else VALIDATION SUCCEEDED
  note right of C
  Step 2 - Authentication towards rtp-sender
  The call to rtp-sender is authenticated.
  A token is first retrieved from mil-auth,
  then the authenticated POST call is executed.
  end note

  C -> MA : POST /token\n(scope: rtp-sender)
  MA --> C : 200 OK\naccess_token

  C -> S : POST /gpd/message\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\nbody: validated message

  alt POST SUCCEEDED
    S --> C : 200 OK\nresponse: RTP body
    C --> EH : ack
    note right of C
    The message has been successfully processed.
    end note

  else POST FAILED (4xx / 5xx / timeout)
    S --> C : error response / timeout
    note right of C
    Even if the POST call fails,
    the message is sent to the Dead letter queue
    for reprocessing and analysis.
    end note

    C -> DLQ : Publish(originalMessage + failure)\nmetadata: httpStatus, errorMessage, timestamp
    DLQ --> C : ack
    C --> EH : ack
  end
end

@enduml